Pre-Game Insights: Cameroon is unbeaten in their last four competitive home matches and will look to extend this run.
Namibia has lost just one of their last seven matches across all competitions while claiming three wins and three draws.
Others: Cameroon and Namibia square off in the 2025 Africa Cup of Nations qualifiers on Saturday.
Cameroon maintained their unbeaten campaign in the 2026 FIFA World Cup qualifiers as they played out a 1-1 draw with Angola.
Namibia were denied a second COSAFA Cup title on July 7 when they fell to a humiliating 7-0 loss against Angola in the final.
